<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-K1lthj0PzI4o1gwQKLysHA" name="design_meth_asset,_tBQ3kOxoEdydutqrlpQKOw" guid="-K1lthj0PzI4o1gwQKLysHA" changeDate="2010-08-27T17:46:52.937-0600" version="7.2.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Following the establishment of the a method library, this task will help in identifying and designing practices. Start&#xD;
    with identifying the scope of this design effort that will determine whether to add a new practice or extend an&#xD;
    existing practice.The designer can determine the practices and plug-ins to be designed.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For&amp;nbsp;each identified practice, the designer will define its method content elements, processes, and capability&#xD;
    patterns as well as guidance and tool mentors. Categorizing the practice elements will help in organizing the practices&#xD;
    as well as smoothing the creation of the practice plug-ins and configuration, which will wrap up this designing effort.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_-zt14KZAEd-GGqaLxOuMZQ" name="Identify scope" guid="_-zt14KZAEd-GGqaLxOuMZQ">
    <sectionDescription>Determine whether to add new practices or extend existing practices (e.g. adding or modifying plug-ins for existing&#xD;
practices).</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Xw0MoKZBEd-GGqaLxOuMZQ" name="Identify practices and plugins" guid="_Xw0MoKZBEd-GGqaLxOuMZQ">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Determine the kind of plug-ins to be created: including standard practices plug-ins, extension to core plug-ins,&#xD;
    process plug-ins which identify capability patterns, and publish plug-ins which specify configurations. &amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_tlD8EKZBEd-GGqaLxOuMZQ" name="Structure practices" guid="_tlD8EKZBEd-GGqaLxOuMZQ">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Structure a practice:&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Define method elements and the relationships between them.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Define processes and capability patterns for the practice&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Identify guidance and tool mentors&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_FzOJMKZCEd-GGqaLxOuMZQ" name="Categorize method elements" guid="_FzOJMKZCEd-GGqaLxOuMZQ"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_IdsLYKZCEd-GGqaLxOuMZQ" name="Create practices, plug-ins, and configurations" guid="_IdsLYKZCEd-GGqaLxOuMZQ">
    <sectionDescription>Add these method&amp;nbsp;assets&amp;nbsp;to the method library.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_lg0_8OxKEd-44czm_ar0ew" name="Evaluate the design" guid="_lg0_8OxKEd-44czm_ar0ew">
    <sectionDescription>Confirm that the design of your method assets conform to the method library architecture. Conduct peer reviews and&#xD;
stakeholder reviews to identify opportunities for improvement. Revise the design as necessary.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>The purpose of this task is to identify and define practices and the relationships between them as well as determine the&#xD;
configuration for publish.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
